Exercise 17.19: Why is it okay to call m[4].str() without first checking
whether m[4] was matched?

Answer:
Calling str is legal since we are comparing the delimiters, so if no there was no match an empty string will be returned

Exercise 17.31: What would happen if we defined b and e inside the do
loop of the game-playing program from this section?

Answer:
We would get the same number each time because a new engine will be created which will cause the first number
is the sequence to be returned.

Exercise 17.32: What would happen if we defined resp inside the loop?

Answer:
The code will not compile since resp will be unidentified in the loop condition.